  "businessLogic": [
    "Determine the featureType from SlotsDTO to route contract-fetching logic.",
    "If featureType is ApyCreate: extract ApyDTO from InternalDataModel, retrieve interest rate and currency via ContractHelperService using MAPPER_ID_INTEREST_RATE and CustomerContract type, then set interestRateCode and currencyCode into SlotsDTO.",
    "If featureType is FundTransfer, MultiCreditTransaction, or MultiDebitTransaction: iterate over each TransferLegContext in TRANSFER_LEG_CONTEXTS, fetch CustomerContract and AccountContract for each leg via ContractHelperService, enrich ReferenceContractDTO with depositAmount from account-level contract, set the contract on each leg, and update TRANSFER_LEG_CONTEXTS in SlotsDTO.",
    "For OpenAccount featureType: parse AccountDTO from current command payload, extract cifId and purposeId, set CIF_ID in SlotsDTO, then retrieve CustomerContract via ContractHelperService.",
    "For AccountClosure or TDAccountPreClosure featureType: extract cifId, purposeId, and accountId from SlotsDTO domain slots, then retrieve AccountContract via ContractHelperService.",
    "Validate that contract details are not null or empty; throw FbpApplicationException with UNABLE_TO_RETRIEVE_CONTRACT_FROM_SOURCE_SYSTEM if missing.",
    "Parse the retrieved contract JSON into ReferenceContractDTO; validate that contractId is not null, throwing FbpValidationException with CONTRACT_DETAILS_DO_NOT_EXIST_FOR_THE_GIVEN_PRODUCT if missing.",
    "For transaction features with a non-null accountId, enrich ReferenceContractDTO with depositAmount by fetching the account-level contract and extracting the depositAmount object (value and currencyCode).",
    "Set the populated ReferenceContractDTO into SlotsDTO under REFERENCE_CONTRACT_PARAMS.",
    "Update CONTRACT_ID and PURPOSE_ID slots in SlotsDTO based on the fetched contract data."
  ],
  "errorConstants": [
    "UNABLE_TO_RETRIEVE_CONTRACT_FROM_SOURCE_SYSTEM",
    "CONTRACT_DETAILS_DO_NOT_EXIST_FOR_THE_GIVEN_PRODUCT"
